        <abstract> 
<p>AG’s review of John Phillips’ book [<hi rend="italic">Life on earth</hi> (1860), in <hi rend="italic">Am. J. Sci.</hi> 2d ser. 31 (1861): 444–9].</p>  
<p>Thinks his experiments will explain <hi rend="italic">Primula</hi> dimorphism.</p> 
            <p>Insect fertilisation of orchids.</p>
            <p>Wishes that the "greatest curse on Earth", slavery, were abolished.</p>
        </abstract>
